A few notes of feedback/constructive criticism before congratulating the incredible quality:

1. The ziploc vacuum seal severely warped the appearance of the bud to the point of it having an undesirable aesthetic making it hard to really see the high quality of the bud which makes it unfortunately harder to resell and upsell. 
Go for the triple mylar bag seal--maintains the aesthetic/textural integrity, provides a solid visual/touch barrier, stealth quality and smell factor.  I would order a half pound or more of this stuff if the beautiful, fluffy bud texture remained intact. 

2. Decent stealth, but could be improved for reputability sake. See end of comment 1.

3. Shipping was prettyy, prettty slow. I was getting nervous that I wouldn't get it before the holidays. Most people are willing to pay more for 3 day express mail, including moui.  

Besides those notes, goodness gracious that is some stanky, nappy fire! I will likely be back especially if the price point remains similar and the dissemination method improves!

Cheers and Merry Christmas/happy holidays/new year!

In plain, material terms, the fair market value for what cosmicbites sent me--not a QP of anything that comes close to amazing nor consisting of huge buds--is tops $300-320.  All I received (besides a couple random, unordered and unwanted $5 truffles) was 100.75 grams! 30.75 grams consisted of small midgrade buds, *nothing at all to write home about*, 24 grams of yellowed schwag, like, basically useless ditch for real, and 46 grams of crumbs, trim and a massive, massive pile of seeds, over 150 in total no joke  This order was 1. not a QP by over 11% on it's face. 2. the vast, heaping majority was an unequivocally inadequate *untrustworthy* version of the advertised listing. A few notes of feedback/constructive criticism before congratulating the incredible quality:

1. The ziploc vacuum seal severely warped the appearance of the bud to the point of it having an undesirable aesthetic making it hard to really see the high quality of the bud which makes it unfortunately harder to resell and upsell. 
Go for the triple mylar bag seal--maintains the aesthetic/textural integrity, provides a solid visual/touch barrier, stealth quality and smell factor.  I would order a half pound or more of this stuff if the beautiful, fluffy bud texture remained intact. 

2. Decent stealth, but could be improved for reputability sake. See end of comment 1.

3. Shipping was prettyy, prettty slow. I was getting nervous that I wouldn't get it before the holidays. Most people are willing to pay more for 3 day express mail, including moui.  

Besides those notes, goodness gracious that is some stanky, nappy fire! I will likely be back especially if the price point remains similar and the dissemination method improves!

Cheers and Merry Christmas/happy holidays/new year!

In plain, material terms, the fair market value for what cosmicbites sent me--not a QP of anything that comes close to amazing nor consisting of huge buds--is tops $300-320.  All I received (besides a couple random, unordered and unwanted $5 truffles) was 100.75 grams! 30.75 grams consisted of small midgrade buds, *nothing at all to write home about*, 24 grams of yellowed schwag, like, basically useless ditch for real, and 46 grams of crumbs, trim and a massive, massive pile of seeds, over 150 in total no joke  This order was 1. not a QP by over 11% on it's face. 2. the vast, heaping majority was an unequivocally inadequate *untrustworthy* version of the advertised listing. I managed to get a decimal point back from this BS bilk of a transaction after disputing their unethical bait and switchery but that resolution is far too lenient for this scamster masquerading as a "trusted vendor".

A few notes of feedback/constructive criticism before congratulating the incredible quality:

1. The ziploc vacuum seal severely warped the appearance of the bud to the point of it having an undesirable aesthetic making it hard to really see the high quality of the bud which makes it unfortunately harder to resell and upsell. 
Go for the triple mylar bag seal--maintains the aesthetic/textural integrity, provides a solid visual/touch barrier, stealth quality and smell factor.  I would order a half pound or more of this stuff if the beautiful, fluffy bud texture remained intact. 

2. Decent stealth, but could be improved for reputability sake. See end of comment 1.

3. Shipping was prettyy, prettty slow. I was getting nervous that I wouldn't get it before the holidays. Most people are willing to pay more for 3 day express mail, including moui.  

Besides those notes, goodness gracious that is some stanky, nappy fire! I will likely be back especially if the price point remains similar and the dissemination method improves!

Cheers and Merry Christmas/happy holidays/new year!
